"""Build aligned face-parsing ROI datasets on a 224x224 canvas.

This script creates local ROI crops from the same aligned 224-space used by the
global face-parsing hybrid preprocessing pipeline. It does not train a model and
does not create or alter data folds.

Key constraints:
* ROI boxes are defined in aligned_rgb 224x224 coordinates, not source-image
  coordinates.
* The script reads global intermediates when available:
  aligned_rgb/{ID}.png, parsing_label/{ID}.png,
  selected_semantic_mask/{ID}.png, final_face_mask/{ID}.png.
* Missing intermediates can be regenerated by reusing the existing strict
  global preprocessing logic: original-coordinate similarity alignment,
  BiSeNet face parsing, selected semantic mask, and hybrid final face mask.
* Both raw ROI and masked ROI are saved as uint8 RGB PNG files after
  aspect-ratio-preserving resize + black padding to a square canvas.
* ImageNet normalization is intentionally not performed here.
"""

